Topic : Multimodal Integration in Neural Network Models

Questions : 
1) What is 'Multimodal Integration'?

2) What are the physiological(empirical) obversations?
  2.1) What are the features of multisensory integration?
  2.2) How is multisensory integration developed?

3) What are the computational models?
  3.1) What are the simple discriptions of these models regarding their computational or methematical methods?
  3.2) How do the models accord with the empirical obversations?
    3.2.1) Are there any experiments that can prove these models to be possible real in brain?
    3.2.2) What are the observed features that are still not modeled in these methods?

4) What are the applications of these models?
  4.1) (potential) applications in robotics?

References[0] :
1) Physiological obversations. (Question 2)
1.1) Features (of developed neurons). (Question 2.1)
**  Stein, B. E., & Stanford, T. R. (2008). Multisensory integration: current issues from the perspective of the single neuron. Nature Reviews Neuroscience, 9(4), 255-266.
*   Kadunce, D. C., Vaughan, J. W., Wallace, M. T., Benedek, G., & Stein, B. E. (1997). Mechanisms of within-and cross-modality suppression in the superior colliculus. Journal of neurophysiology, 78(6), 2834-2847.

1.2) Development. (Question 2.2)
**  Wallace, M. T., Carriere, B. N., Perrault, T. J., Vaughan, J. W., & Stein, B. E. (2006). The development of cortical multisensory integration. The Journal of neuroscience, 26(46), 11844-11849.
*   Yu, L., Rowland, B. A., Xu, J., & Stein, B. E. (2013). Multisensory plasticity in adulthood: cross-modal experience enhances neuronal excitability and exposes silent inputs. Journal of neurophysiology, 109(2), 464-474.

2) Models (Question 3)
*** Cuppini, C., Magosso, E., Rowland, B., Stein, B., & Ursino, M. (2012). Hebbian mechanisms help explain development of multisensory integration in the superior colliculus: a neural network model. Biological cybernetics, 106(11-12), 691-713.
*** Cai, K., & Shen, J. (2011, October). Continuous attractor neural network model of multisensory integration. In System Science, Engineering Design and Manufacturing Informatization (ICSEM), 2011 International Conference on (Vol. 2, pp. 352-355). IEEE.
*** Rowland, B. A., Stanford, T. R., & Stein, B. E. (2007). A model of the neural mechanisms underlying multisensory integration in the superior colliculus. Perception-London, 36(10), 1431-1444.
*** Patton, P. E., & Anastasio, T. J. (2003). Modeling cross-modal enhancement and modality-specific suppression in multisensory neurons. Neural computation, 15(4), 783-810.

3) Applications (Question 4)
